# Privacy Policy — Shuffle All

**Effective Date:** April 9, 2026

Shuffle All ("the App") is a free Android application that generates randomized playlists from your Spotify library. This Privacy Policy explains how your information is handled.

## Information the App Accesses

To function, the App connects to the Spotify API using credentials you provide (your own Spotify Client ID and Client Secret). Through this connection the App accesses:

- Your list of followed artists on Spotify
- Track and album metadata for those artists
- Your Spotify account display name (for authentication purposes)

## Data Storage and Processing

**All data stays on your device.** The App does not operate any server or backend service. Specifically:

- Your Spotify Client ID and Client Secret are stored locally on your device and are only used to authenticate directly with Spotify's servers.
- Playlist data, artist cooldown history, and app preferences are stored locally on your device using Android's SharedPreferences.
- The App includes a diagnostics export tool; any exported data is saved to your device and is never transmitted automatically.

## Data the App Does NOT Collect

- The App does not collect analytics, usage data, or crash reports.
- The App does not use advertising SDKs or tracking technologies.
- The App does not transmit any personal data to the developer or any third party (other than Spotify, as described above).

## Third-Party Services

The App communicates solely with the **Spotify Web API** to retrieve your music library data. Your use of Spotify is governed by [Spotify's Privacy Policy](https://www.spotify.com/privacy). No other third-party services are used.

## Children's Privacy

The App is not directed at children under the age of 13 and does not knowingly collect information from children.

